(6228, 1, '2016-12-29 18:03:30', '2016-12-29 18:03:30', '[full_width_section text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/2" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text]Companies are adopting Hadoop as a lower cost, higher performance alternative to proprietary data warehousing and are now using data lakes for storing both structured and unstructured data, which quite often contains sensitive information. Data being ingested and residing in the data lake needs to be accessed by different teams including business analysts, data scientists, developers, and others in the enterprise. In many cases, it also needs to be shared with partners and customers externally.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/2" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text]Enforcing existing enterprise security models in this new paradigm has proven difficult because Hadoop was not designed with security in mind and the current set of alternative data encryption and tokenization products require unacceptable trade-offs between security, performance and cost. The NuCypher platform allows you to easily apply existing roles and user privileges to your data lakes, without sacrificing performance or increasing costs.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section image_url="6411" bg_pos="Center Center" background_color="#01579b" text_color="light" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][testimonial_slider style="default" autorotate="6500"][testimonial name="Heather Wilson, CDO of AIG, a global insurance organization" quote="My job is to create a data infrastructure so that employees can access and use all of this data  to make it available in a way that doesnt take away from them doing their jobs." id="1483386688434-7241e-3ca5" title="Testimonial" tab_id="1483392985665-3"][/testimonial][/testimonial_slider][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="light" top_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="left-right" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">A Scalable Policy-Based Approach To Ensure The Right Users Have Access To The Right Data</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="light" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="left-right" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/1" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_row_inner equal_height="yes" text_align="left"][vc_column_inner column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color="#01579b" background_color_opacity="1" width="1/4"][image_with_animation image_url="6446" alignment="center" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483393447012{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h5>Multi-Tenant Administration</h5>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color="#0277bd" background_color_opacity="1" width="1/4"][image_with_animation image_url="6447" alignment="center" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483393464100{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h5>Revocable Access</h5>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color="#0288d1" background_color_opacity="1" width="1/4"][image_with_animation image_url="6448" alignment="center" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483393474553{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h5>Policy-Based Encryption</h5>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner boxed="true" column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color="#039be5" background_color_opacity="1" width="1/4"][image_with_animation image_url="6445" alignment="center" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483393485314{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h5>Separation of Duties</h5>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483393543794{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">On-Premise or In-The-Cloud: No Problem</h2>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: left;">Multi-Tenant Administration</h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]NuCypher allows permissions on different data sets to be delegated to different administrators. You can extend Hadoop to more users, securely store sensitive data with non-sensitive data, and share it with users across all departments and multiple organizations through multi-tenant authorization and fine-grained access controls.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][image_with_animation image_url="6446" alignment="center" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][image_with_animation image_url="6447" alignment="center" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483393591420{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Adds and Removes User Access in Real-Time</h2>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: left;">Enterprise User Synchronization</h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]Access policies are inherited from the Hadoop management platform and tied to LDAP/AD/Kerberos to maintain real-time user provisioning and de-provisioning synchronization.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483393638138{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Block Sensitive Data - Analyze Valuable Data</h2>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: left;">Policy-Based Granular Encryption</h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]Control who can use data, where they can use it, and when they can use it. By sharing data with granular permissions, third parties or other departments within an organization can only decrypt the specific slices of the data (i.e. columns and fields) which they are allowed to access.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][image_with_animation image_url="6448" alignment="center" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][image_with_animation image_url="6445" alignment="center" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483393984218{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Maintain Access Policies To Protect Against Internal Threats</h2>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: left;">Enforce Separation of Duties</h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]Keep administrators and users in their swim lanes to meet compliance and governance requirements. Enforce role-based access controls (RBAC) that are granular enough to enable least privilege permissions and enforce separation of duties.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/full_width_section]', 'Data Sharing and Multi-Tenancy', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'data-sharing-and-multi-tenancy', '', '', '2017-01-04 18:16:54', '2017-01-04 18:16:54', '', 0, 'http://nucypher.com/?page_id=6228', 7, 'page', '', 0),
