(6360, 1, '2017-01-03 01:34:27', '2017-01-03 01:34:27', '[full_width_section text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/2" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text]Data governance and compliance requirements are growing in regulated industries such as healthcare, financial services, and retail due to the accelerating frequency and scope of data breaches. Big data presents tremendous challenges when it comes to maintaining regulatory compliance and adhering to data sovereignty regulations. As traditional data repositories with strictly defined compliance rules morph into data lakes filled with a mix of data, controlling access to sensitive information becomes increasingly difficult. And with more users leveraging and processing the data, it frequently gets transformed into new forms of data with varying levels of sensitivity. The totality of these activities makes it difficult to perform compliance functions when data is constantly changing, moving between locations, and being access by disparate users.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/2" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text]NuCypher provides data-centric security that follows the data wherever it goes and easily integrates into your security and compliance policies to bring data lakes into compliance with corporate and regulatory data protection initiatives including GDPR, HIPAA, HITECH, and PCI. By sharing data with granular permission, third parties or other departments within an organization can only access the specific slices of data which they are allowed to decrypt, allowing you to restrict access to sensitive data while at the same time freeing the data needed to deliver business insights.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#454156" text_color="light" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][testimonial_slider style="default" autorotate="6500"][testimonial name=" Chief Architect at Global Financial Institution" quote="My assignment is to make the data more accessible and available, to accelerate speed to insight, yet at the same time be aware of the regulatory environment and the need for strong data governance. Other products we looked failed to address compliance requirements without significant downtime and performance constraints- NuCypher allows us to reduce our data risk and increase our business agility." id="1483386688434-770f2-70a8" title="Testimonial" tab_id="1483407171586-7"][/testimonial][/testimonial_slider][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="light" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="left-right" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/1" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_row_inner equal_height="yes" text_align="left"][vc_column_inner column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color="#01579b" background_color_opacity="1" width="1/4"][image_with_animation image_url="6299" alignment="" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483390617043{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h5>Encryption of Sensitive Data</h5>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color="#0277bd" background_color_opacity="1" width="1/4"][image_with_animation image_url="6299" alignment="" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483390762481{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h5>Role-Based Access Control</h5>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color="#0288d1" background_color_opacity="1" width="1/4"][image_with_animation image_url="6299" alignment="" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483390774334{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h5>Boundary Control</h5>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner boxed="true" column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color="#039be5" background_color_opacity="1" width="1/4"][image_with_animation image_url="6299" alignment="" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483390782689{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h5>Key Management</h5>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483392367585{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Encryption of Sensitive Data Everywhere It Goes</h2>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: left;"><strong>End-to End Encryption of Sensitive Data</strong></h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]The NuCypher platform supports granular encryption, allowing fine-grained decryption permissions both for internal employees and external partners and customers. in multi-tenant cloud environments and centralized data lakes. And it works seamlessly across multi-tenant environments and centralized data lakes as well as on-premise and in private, hybrid, and public clouds.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][image_with_animation image_url="6299" alignment="" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][image_with_animation image_url="6299" alignment="" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483392253036{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Fine Grained Access Control</h2>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: left;"><strong>Role-Based Access Control</strong></h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]This gives you the ability to maintain a separation of duties between administrative and authorized user access. NuCypher prevents unauthorized access and meets privacy, security, and compliance requirements.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483392259394{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Border Patrol for Your Data</h2>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: left;"><strong>Boundary Control</strong></h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]This maintains data sovereignty. With NuCypher, you control not only where your data resides but who can access it, and from where. Define access controls based on geographic area, sets of nodes meeting certain compliance or regulatory requirements, or a number of other factors, to easily comply with data sovereignty requirements and protect against both insider threats and external breaches.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][image_with_animation image_url="6299" alignment="" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][image_with_animation image_url="6299" alignment="" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483392266454{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">FIPS 140-2 Compliant Key Management</h2>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: left;"><strong>Military Strength Key Management</strong></h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]It is easilyintegrated into the NuCypher platform through integrations with leading Hardware Security Module vendors. Keys are managed through policy settings, making the system easy to use. NuCypher offers ultra-efficient key rotation, where administrators can set policies to re-key automatically in accordance with industry regulations like PCI or with internal guidelines.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/full_width_section]', 'Proxy Re-Encryption', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6222-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-03 01:34:27', '2017-01-03 01:34:27', '', 6222, 'http://nucypher.com/2017/01/03/6222-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(6361, 1, '2017-01-03 01:44:43', '2017-01-03 01:44:43', '[full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text]NuCyphers revolutionary access control enables organizations to use military strength data encryption to protect large unstructured data sets in the cloud or on-premise, without sacrificing security or performance.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#01579b" text_color="light" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][testimonial_slider style="default" autorotate="6500"][testimonial name="David, NICS Lab" quote="Quote from David/NICS Lab about PRE technology potential." id="1483386688434-770f2-70a8" title="Testimonial" tab_id="1483407171586-7"][/testimonial][/testimonial_slider][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/1" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483407520985{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">The Use Of Cryptography Dates Back To Caesar</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]In Roman times, messengers were used as the transmission mechanism, and encryption helped protect the message in case the messenger was captured. A second messenger was used to carry the decryption scheme. While the transmission mechanism has changed from human beings to data packets  the core challenge remains.\r\n\r\nIn todays enterprise, cryptography is vital to protect the secrecy and integrity of transmitted and stored information. However, traditional cryptographic schemes do not scale well, and arent suited to support big data platforms where huge numbers of users process massive amounts of data. Most legacy encryption products were designed for static relational databases and lack the ability to scale and perform well in highly dynamic, petabyte-scale, distributed computing architectures. Very few are optimized for big data platforms and distributed file systems like HDFS. And certainly not in cloud environments.\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to securing big data in the enterprise, existing encryption solutions are insufficient in many ways. Hadoop\'s native open-source transparent data encryption (TDE) lacks basic key rotation capabilities and forces manual, time-consuming workarounds - making it difficult to fit into existing enterprise security infrastructures and extremely difficult to comply with standards that require key rotation such as PCI. This also creates security risks when used in the cloud because it leaves keys exposed and unprotected in the providers infrastructure.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/1" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483407816087{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">[icon enable_animation="true" color="Accent-Color" animation_speed="Slow" icon_size="60" animation_delay="" image="basic_lock.svg"] You Cant Use Data You Cant Unlock</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]In a single-user cryptographic file system, access control is straightforward. The user creates all the keys protecting content and there is no key distribution problem. With group sharing in cryptographic storage, group members must communicate with content owners to obtain decryption keys for accessing files - creating operational barriers and security risks that render this method unusable in big data environments which need to share access to massive amounts of data among many users. At its core, the NuCypher system relies on providing temporary keys to encrypt and decrypt the data and managing who has the rights to use these keys. NuCypher uses a breakthrough re-encryption scheme developed to secure distributed storage among many users.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483392259394{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Border Patrol for Your Data</h2>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: left;"><strong>Boundary Control</strong></h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]This maintains data sovereignty. With NuCypher, you control not only where your data resides but who can access it, and from where. Define access controls based on geographic area, sets of nodes meeting certain compliance or regulatory requirements, or a number of other factors, to easily comply with data sovereignty requirements and protect against both insider threats and external breaches.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][image_with_animation image_url="6299" alignment="" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][image_with_animation image_url="6299" alignment="" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483392266454{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">FIPS 140-2 Compliant Key Management</h2>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: left;"><strong>Military Strength Key Management</strong></h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]It is easilyintegrated into the NuCypher platform through integrations with leading Hardware Security Module vendors. Keys are managed through policy settings, making the system easy to use. NuCypher offers ultra-efficient key rotation, where administrators can set policies to re-key automatically in accordance with industry regulations like PCI or with internal guidelines.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/full_width_section]', 'Proxy Re-Encryption', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6222-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-03 01:44:43', '2017-01-03 01:44:43', '', 6222, 'http://nucypher.com/2017/01/03/6222-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(6362, 1, '2017-01-03 02:07:01', '2017-01-03 02:07:01', '[full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text]NuCyphers revolutionary access control enables organizations to use military strength data encryption to protect large unstructured data sets in the cloud or on-premise, without sacrificing security or performance.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#01579b" text_color="light" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][testimonial_slider style="default" autorotate="6500"][testimonial name="David, NICS Lab" quote="Quote from David/NICS Lab about PRE technology potential." id="1483386688434-770f2-70a8" title="Testimonial" tab_id="1483407171586-7"][/testimonial][/testimonial_slider][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483407520985{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">The Use Of Cryptography Dates Back To Caesar</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]In Roman times, messengers were used as the transmission mechanism, and encryption helped protect the message in case the messenger was captured. A second messenger was used to carry the decryption scheme. While the transmission mechanism has changed from human beings to data packets  the core challenge remains.\r\n\r\nIn todays enterprise, cryptography is vital to protect the secrecy and integrity of transmitted and stored information. However, traditional cryptographic schemes do not scale well, and arent suited to support big data platforms where huge numbers of users process massive amounts of data. Most legacy encryption products were designed for static relational databases and lack the ability to scale and perform well in highly dynamic, petabyte-scale, distributed computing architectures. Very few are optimized for big data platforms and distributed file systems like HDFS. And certainly not in cloud environments.\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to securing big data in the enterprise, existing encryption solutions are insufficient in many ways. Hadoop\'s native open-source transparent data encryption (TDE) lacks basic key rotation capabilities and forces manual, time-consuming workarounds - making it difficult to fit into existing enterprise security infrastructures and extremely difficult to comply with standards that require key rotation such as PCI. This also creates security risks when used in the cloud because it leaves keys exposed and unprotected in the providers infrastructure.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][nectar_icon icon_family="linea" enable_animation="true" animation_speed="medium" icon_style="default" icon_color="Accent-Color" icon_padding="10px" icon_linea="icon-basic-lock" icon_size="60"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483409122309{padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">You Cant Use Data You Cant Unlock</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]In a single-user cryptographic file system, access control is straightforward. The user creates all the keys protecting content and there is no key distribution problem. With group sharing in cryptographic storage, group members must communicate with content owners to obtain decryption keys for accessing files - creating operational barriers and security risks that render this method unusable in big data environments which need to share access to massive amounts of data among many users. At its core, the NuCypher system relies on providing temporary keys to encrypt and decrypt the data and managing who has the rights to use these keys. NuCypher uses a breakthrough re-encryption scheme developed to secure distributed storage among many users.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][nectar_icon icon_family="linea" enable_animation="true" animation_speed="medium" icon_style="default" icon_color="Accent-Color" icon_padding="10px" icon_linea="icon-basic-magnifier" icon_size="60"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483409168321{padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Delegated Proxy Re-encryption Is The Secret Sauce</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]Secure distribution of encryption keys is one of the major flaws of traditional encryption schemes. NuCypher is designed to enforce premise-based key issuance, so that keys never leave your control. It issues temporary keys so your master key is kept secure and because the access control server doesnt store the master secret, it cannot decrypt the keys it stores at-will. The master secret key can be stored offline, by a content owner who uses it only to generate the re-encryption keys used by the access control server\r\n\r\nAs is latency and downtime, NuCypher is a cryptographically enforced access control system based on proxy re-encryption where data remains encrypted until it is needed for processing. Data is stored encrypted in the cluster and the owner can delegate access rights to the compute cluster for processing. By delegating encryption operations to the cluster, NuCypher eliminates latency and downtime.\r\n\r\nAs well as network reliability and data availability, one of the problems with storing encrypted data in the cloud is revoking access rights from users. A user whose permission is revoked will still retain the previously issued keys, and thus can still decrypt data in the cloud. As a result, the data must be re-encrypted. However, since a cloud computing environment is comprised of many cloud servers, such commands may not be received and executed by all of the cloud servers due to unreliable network communications. Because NuCyher delegates operations to the cluster these issues are mitigated. With NuCypher Hadoop, processing doesn\'t require communication between compute nodes and the key management service (KMS). This means the KMS doesn\'t have to stay online during a job, removing latency bottlenecks and slow requests over the network.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][nectar_icon icon_family="linea" enable_animation="true" animation_speed="medium" icon_style="default" icon_color="Accent-Color" icon_padding="10px" icon_linea="icon-arrows-glide-horizontal" icon_size="60"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483409226462{padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Which Means No More Tradeoffs Between Security, Performance, And Cost</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]With secure, scalable access delegation and key rotation you can provide your administrators, developers, testers, researchers, and analysts with always-on access to data and enable analytics to be performed on data located across large and complex environments - on-premise, private, public, or hybrid clouds.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section]', 'Proxy Re-Encryption', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6222-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-03 02:07:01', '2017-01-03 02:07:01', '', 6222, 'http://nucypher.com/2017/01/03/6222-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
