(6414, 1, '2017-01-03 21:33:59', '2017-01-03 21:33:59', '[full_width_section text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/2" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text]Data governance and compliance requirements are growing in regulated industries such as healthcare, financial services, and retail due to the accelerating frequency and scope of data breaches. Big data presents tremendous challenges when it comes to maintaining regulatory compliance and adhering to data sovereignty regulations. As traditional data repositories with strictly defined compliance rules morph into data lakes filled with a mix of data, controlling access to sensitive information becomes increasingly difficult. And with more users leveraging and processing the data, it frequently gets transformed into new forms of data with varying levels of sensitivity. The totality of these activities makes it difficult to perform compliance functions when data is constantly changing, moving between locations, and being access by disparate users.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/2" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text]NuCypher provides data-centric security that follows the data wherever it goes and easily integrates into your security and compliance policies to bring data lakes into compliance with corporate and regulatory data protection initiatives including GDPR, HIPAA, HITECH, and PCI. By sharing data with granular permission, third parties or other departments within an organization can only access the specific slices of data which they are allowed to decrypt, allowing you to restrict access to sensitive data while at the same time freeing the data needed to deliver business insights.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section image_url="6411" bg_pos="Center Center" background_color="#01579b" text_color="light" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][testimonial_slider style="default" autorotate="6500"][testimonial name=" Chief Architect at Global Financial Institution" quote="My assignment is to make the data more accessible and available, to accelerate speed to insight, yet at the same time be aware of the regulatory environment and the need for strong data governance. Other products we looked failed to address compliance requirements without significant downtime and performance constraints- NuCypher allows us to reduce our data risk and increase our business agility." id="1483382588028-2b3ff-516a" title="Testimonial" tab_id="1483386688434-7"][/testimonial][/testimonial_slider][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="