(6416, 1, '2017-01-03 21:37:19', '2017-01-03 21:37:19', '[full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="80"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483405497480{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Risk Mitigation Can Lead To Project Bottlenecks and Delays</h2>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;">Organizations Managing Complex Big Data Projects Face 4 Key Challenges</h4>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;"></h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][vc_row type="full_width_background" full_screen_row_position="middle" bg_color="#ffffff" scene_position="center" text_color="dark" text_align="left" bottom_padding="90" overlay_strength="0.3"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/4" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][nectar_icon icon_family="linea" enable_animation="true" animation_speed="medium" icon_style="default" icon_color="Accent-Color" icon_padding="10px" icon_linea="icon-basic-clockwise" icon_size="60"][vc_column_text]<strong>Bringing their big data projects and products to market quickly</strong>,<strong></strong>while ensuring the data is secure, reliable, and compliant with established regulations and/or internal security policies and standards.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/4" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][nectar_icon icon_family="linea" enable_animation="true" animation_speed="medium" icon_style="default" icon_color="Accent-Color" icon_padding="10px" icon_linea="icon-basic-share" icon_size="60"][vc_column_text]<strong>Supporting multiple teams and projects that are large</strong>, geographically distributed, and a mix of internal and outsourced resources - in the face of constantly changing requirements.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/4" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][nectar_icon icon_family="linea" enable_animation="true" animation_speed="medium" icon_style="default" icon_color="Accent-Color" icon_padding="10px" icon_linea="icon-arrows-glide-horizontal" icon_size="60"][vc_column_text]<strong>Balancing business initiatives and security requirements with project speed and quality</strong>, in a way that maximizes profitability.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/4" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][nectar_icon icon_family="linea" enable_animation="true" animation_speed="medium" icon_style="default" icon_color="Accent-Color" icon_padding="10px" icon_linea="icon-basic-elaboration-document-check" icon_size="60"][vc_column_text]<strong>Using data at scale, across locations, and increasing time to insight</strong>, to boost innovation and increase business agility.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][full_width_section image_url="6411" bg_pos="Center Center" background_color="#01579b" text_color="light" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][testimonial_slider style="default" autorotate="6500"][testimonial name="Chief Data Officer of a large financial services company" quote="In order for data to eventually be an asset, it must no longer be a liability." id="1483386688434-732e6-f100" title="Testimonial" tab_id="1483405214482-0"][/testimonial][/testimonial_slider][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="65" bottom_padding="5"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483405321927{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">NuCypher Helps You Bring Big Data Projects and Products Online Faster and More Securely</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="5" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/4" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][image_with_animation image_url="6299" alignment="" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="3/4" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483406534313{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">1.</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Reduces breach risks with end-end protection of data at-rest and in-flight</strong>, surpassing compliance and governance requirements. NuCypher inherits existing access policies to quickly provision users and data access.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="5" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/4" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][image_with_animation image_url="6299" alignment="" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="3/4" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483406598182{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">2.</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Secure extend Hadoop to more users and multi-tenant environments.</strong>Securely store sensitive data alongside non-sensitive data in encrypted data lakes and share it with users across different departments and organizations with fine-grained access controls.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="5" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/4" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][image_with_animation image_url="6299" alignment="" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="3/4" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483406629846{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">3.</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Enable elastic computing and leverage the cloud.</strong> Meet compliance and governance requirements, eliminate performance issues, and support multi-tenancy - all without jeopardizing security. NuCypher flexibly adapts to the fast-growing big data and Hadoop ecosystem, offering unparalleled performance and scalability with zero impact on analytics.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="5" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/4" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][image_with_animation image_url="6299" alignment="" animation="Fade In" box_shadow="none" max_width="100%"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="3/4" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483406656363{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">4.</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Fast, reliable protection that plugs in to your existing infrastructure.</strong>Proxy re-encryption optimizes performance by providing secure, always-on access to your data scientists and analysts without lags, downtime, or fear of unauthorized access. Near-instantaneous key rotation means no encryption zone downtime and the key management service is no longer a performance bottleneck.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/full_width_section]', 'Data Migration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6224-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-03 21:37:19', '2017-01-03 21:37:19', '', 6224, 'http://nucypher.com/2017/01/03/6224-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(6417, 1, '2017-01-03 21:40:50', '2017-01-03 21:40:50', '[full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text]NuCyphers revolutionary access control enables organizations to use military strength data encryption to protect large unstructured data sets in the cloud or on-premise, without sacrificing security or performance.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section image_url="6411" bg_pos="Center Center" background_color="#01579b" text_color="light" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][testimonial_slider style="default" autorotate="6500"][testimonial name="David, NICS Lab" quote="Quote from David/NICS Lab about PRE technology potential." id="1483386688434-770f2-70a8" title="Testimonial" tab_id="1483407171586-7"][/testimonial][/testimonial_slider][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483407520985{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">The Use Of Cryptography Dates Back To Caesar</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]In Roman times, messengers were used as the transmission mechanism, and encryption helped protect the message in case the messenger was captured. A second messenger was used to carry the decryption scheme. While the transmission mechanism has changed from human beings to data packets  the core challenge remains.\r\n\r\nIn todays enterprise, cryptography is vital to protect the secrecy and integrity of transmitted and stored information. However, traditional cryptographic schemes do not scale well, and arent suited to support big data platforms where huge numbers of users process massive amounts of data. Most legacy encryption products were designed for static relational databases and lack the ability to scale and perform well in highly dynamic, petabyte-scale, distributed computing architectures. Very few are optimized for big data platforms and distributed file systems like HDFS. And certainly not in cloud environments.\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to securing big data in the enterprise, existing encryption solutions are insufficient in many ways. Hadoop\'s native open-source transparent data encryption (TDE) lacks basic key rotation capabilities and forces manual, time-consuming workarounds - making it difficult to fit into existing enterprise security infrastructures and extremely difficult to comply with standards that require key rotation such as PCI. This also creates security risks when used in the cloud because it leaves keys exposed and unprotected in the providers infrastructure.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][nectar_icon icon_family="linea" enable_animation="true" animation_speed="medium" icon_style="default" icon_color="Accent-Color" icon_padding="10px" icon_linea="icon-basic-lock" icon_size="60"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483409122309{padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">You Cant Use Data You Cant Unlock</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]In a single-user cryptographic file system, access control is straightforward. The user creates all the keys protecting content and there is no key distribution problem. With group sharing in cryptographic storage, group members must communicate with content owners to obtain decryption keys for accessing files - creating operational barriers and security risks that render this method unusable in big data environments which need to share access to massive amounts of data among many users. At its core, the NuCypher system relies on providing temporary keys to encrypt and decrypt the data and managing who has the rights to use these keys. NuCypher uses a breakthrough re-encryption scheme developed to secure distributed storage among many users.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section background_color="#ffffff" text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][nectar_icon icon_family="linea" enable_animation="true" animation_speed="medium" icon_style="default" icon_color="Accent-Color" icon_padding="10px" icon_linea="icon-basic-magnifier" icon_size="60"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483409168321{padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Delegated Proxy Re-encryption Is The Secret Sauce</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]Secure distribution of encryption keys is one of the major flaws of traditional encryption schemes. NuCypher is designed to enforce premise-based key issuance, so that keys never leave your control. It issues temporary keys so your master key is kept secure and because the access control server doesnt store the master secret, it cannot decrypt the keys it stores at-will. The master secret key can be stored offline, by a content owner who uses it only to generate the re-encryption keys used by the access control server\r\n\r\nAs is latency and downtime, NuCypher is a cryptographically enforced access control system based on proxy re-encryption where data remains encrypted until it is needed for processing. Data is stored encrypted in the cluster and the owner can delegate access rights to the compute cluster for processing. By delegating encryption operations to the cluster, NuCypher eliminates latency and downtime.\r\n\r\nAs well as network reliability and data availability, one of the problems with storing encrypted data in the cloud is revoking access rights from users. A user whose permission is revoked will still retain the previously issued keys, and thus can still decrypt data in the cloud. As a result, the data must be re-encrypted. However, since a cloud computing environment is comprised of many cloud servers, such commands may not be received and executed by all of the cloud servers due to unreliable network communications. Because NuCyher delegates operations to the cluster these issues are mitigated. With NuCypher Hadoop, processing doesn\'t require communication between compute nodes and the key management service (KMS). This means the KMS doesn\'t have to stay online during a job, removing latency bottlenecks and slow requests over the network.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section][full_width_section text_color="dark" top_padding="90" bottom_padding="90"][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="2/3" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][nectar_icon icon_family="linea" enable_animation="true" animation_speed="medium" icon_style="default" icon_color="Accent-Color" icon_padding="10px" icon_linea="icon-arrows-glide-horizontal" icon_size="60"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1483409226462{padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<h2 style="text-align: left;">Which Means No More Tradeoffs Between Security, Performance, And Cost</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]With secure, scalable access delegation and key rotation you can provide your administrators, developers, testers, researchers, and analysts with always-on access to data and enable analytics to be performed on data located across large and complex environments - on-premise, private, public, or hybrid clouds.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column column_padding="no-extra-padding" column_padding_position="all" background_color_opacity="1" background_hover_color_opacity="1" width="1/6" tablet_text_alignment="default" phone_text_alignment="default"][/vc_column][/full_width_section]', 'Proxy Re-Encryption', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6222-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-01-03 21:40:50', '2017-01-03 21:40:50', '', 6222, 'http://nucypher.com/2017/01/03/6222-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
